1.1 Multi-Currency Support
Requirement:
The system must support defining term deposit products across multiple currencies. EUR is
required at launch; the architecture must allow future currencies based on internal roadmap
without major structural changes.
Acceptance Criteria:
● System allows EUR product creation at launch.
● Additional currencies can be enabled through configuration only.
● All modules (accruals, capitalisation, postings, reporting) support multi-currency.
UAT Test Cases:
1. Create EUR product
○ Steps: Log in as an admin user, navigate to the product setup section, create a
product in EUR, and save the configuration.
○ Expected: The product is successfully created, appears in the product catalogue,
and can be used to create deposits in EUR; accrual / capitalisation / posting /
reporting use the correct currency..
2. Enable new currency via configuration
○ Steps: Admin adds a new currency (e.g. AED) in configuration and create
product using AED.
○ Expected: System allows product creation; deposits can be opened in AED;
accrual / capitalisation / posting / reporting use the correct currency.

